data.title: Bishkek air route opened
data.text:
The first flight of Azerbaijan Airlines (AZAL) along the Baku-Bishkek route was launched on 26 October 2014. The Azerbaijani delegation comprised of the representatives of ministries and departments, business community and media arrived in the Manas international airport and were met by the First Deputy Prime Minister of Kyrgyzstan Tayirbek Sarpashev, Azerbaijani Ambassador to Kyrgyzstan Hidayat Orujov and members of the Azerbaijani diaspora in Kyrgyzstan.

Speaking at the ceremony, the First Deputy Prime Minister of Kyrgyzstan Tayirbek Sarpashev, Azerbaijani Ambassador to Kyrgyzstan Hidayat Orujov and member of the Milli Mejlis Fattah Heydarov stressed the importance of this air route. In particular, Sarpashev said that the decision to launch direct flights between the capitals of the two friendly countries is a positive step in strengthening bilateral relations. Mr. Hidayat Orujov highlighted that the flight had been opened on the personal instructions of the President Ilham Aliyev.

The flights will be operating on the A-320 aircraft twice per week on Sundays and Tuesdays.
